snippet.textDisplay: A console, any console, IS just a computing device, and therefore a computer, therefore a PC. XBOX and PlayStation consoles have always been 'PCs'. But is is a console. It does not become more of a PC because its shape changed. It is the same thing on the inside as it always has been, with upgraded hardware. Calling it a PC suddenly because it is now more square seems silly to me. I happen to like the new shape, a lot. I don't call that new shape 'PC' suddenly - it is still classified as a console because it is meant for dedicated gaming and not for general personal computing. No, it is not a PC because it has a more boxlike shape than its predecessors.
